712053f-b.title: Manhattan: 33rd Street (West) - 7th Avenue
712053f-b.text:

west of Seventh Avenue, showing the rear of the Greyhound
Bus Terminal and surrounding features. This transportation
facility runs thru to 34th Street, in the center of the
block bounded by Seventh and Eighth Avenues. Beyond the
latter thoroughfare are the outstanding Printing Crafts Bldg.
and the Hotel New Yorker.

712056f-a.title: Manhattan: 33rd Street (West) - 7th Avenue
712056f-a.text:
West 33rd Street, north side, betwecn Eighth and Seventh Aves. View
shows empty lots utilized as a bus terminal, with an entrance on West 34th
Street.
September 24, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
According to the New York Tims of December 7, 1936 these vacant
1ots, Nos. 225 to 33, will be improved with a 1-story theatre and store
building that will extend through to 234-236 West 34th Street.
